  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD047996",
      "title": "Autophosphorylation of Tousled-like kinases (TLK1 and TLK2) regulates recruitment to damaged chromatin via PCNA interaction (Tandem Affinity Purification coupled to LC-MS/MS of SFB-TLK1 WT and TLK2 WT)",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "S-protein-2xFLAG-Streptavidin binding peptide (SFB)-tagged TLK1 or SFB-TLK2 were transfected into 4x 15 cm plates of HEK293T cells. Cells were harvested 24 hours after transfection using NETN buffer (150 mM NaCl, 0.5 mM EDTA, 20 mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 0.5% NP-40) supplemented with 2 \u00b5g/mL aprotinin (Thermo, AAJ60237MB) and 5 \u00b5g/mL pepstatin A (Thermo, PI78432) at 4\u00baC for 20 minutes. Lysates were centrifuged at 9,000 x g, 4\u00baC for 20 minutes to yield supernatant as soluble fraction. Soluble fractions were incubated with streptavidin sepharose (200 \u00b5l) (GE Healthcare, GE17-5113-01) at 4\u00baC for 1 hour followed by washing with NETN buffer three times. The protein complexes were eluted with 2 mg/mL biotin at 4\u00baC for 1 hour. The eluents were then incubated with S-protein agarose (EMD Millipore, 69704-3) overnight at 4\u00baC, washed three times with NETN buffer, and eluted in 1x Laemmli buffer.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "TAP samples were processed using standard short-run, in-gel trypsin digestion protocols. Protein samples were electrophoresed on a pre-cast 4-20% tris-glycine gel from Invitrogen for 5 minutes at 300V. Proteins were stained with GelCode Safe according to the manufacturer's instructions. A single gel band corresponding to the region between the well and the dye front was excised and cut into small pieces. The excised gel band was destained 3x with a solution of 50 mM ammonium bicarbonate and 50% methanol for 1 hour each wash. Proteins were reduced by addition of 10 mM TCEP for 30 minutes at 37\u00baC. Thiol groups were alkylated by addition of 50 mM Iodoacetamide for 1 hour at room temp, while protected from light. Gel bands were washed by alternating 100 mM ammonium bicarbonate and acetonitrile 3 times. Bands were dehydrated by acetonitrile and digested with Promega, Sequencing grade Trypsin in 50 mM ammonium bicarbonate at 37\u00baC over night. The following day samples were acidified by addition of 0.5% formic acid to a final concentration of 0.1% and desalted over a Water's C18 SepPak. Desalted samples were dried by SpeedVac and stored until ready for LC-MS/MS analysis.  Dried samples were resuspended in 0.1% formic acid and injected onto an in-line, Ultimate 3000 RSLCnano for reverse phase HPLC. The 150 x 0.075 mm column was packed with Xselect CSH C18 2.5\u00b5M resin and peptides were eluted into an Orbitrap Fusion Tribrid mass spectrometer with a 100-min gradient of 97:3 (0.1% formic acid and 0.5% acetonitrile: 0.1% formic acid and 99.9% acetonitrile) to 67:33. Peptides were ionized by electrospray at 2.2 kV. Precursor ions were collected at a resolution of 240,000 in the Orbitrap over a 375 - 1,500 m/z range. DDA of the top 10 precursors was used to select ions for HCD fragmentation with a normalized collision energy between 28.0 and 31.0. Fragment ions between 200 - 1,400 m/z were measured in the ion trap.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Protein identifications were performed in Mascot by searching the Homo sapiens UniProtKB database downloaded on 03-16-2019. Search conditions were set to a parent ion tolerance of 3 ppm and a fragment ion tolerance of 0.5 Da. Carbamidomethylation of cysteine was set as a fixed modification and oxidation of methionine, acetylation of peptide N-termini, and phosphorylation of serine, threonine, and tyrosine were selected as variable modifications. Scaffold was used to validate protein and peptide identifications. Proteins and peptides were considered true identifications if they exhibited less than 1.0% false discovery by Scaffold's local false discovery algorithm.",
